# Implementation Plan - Restore Auto-Start Functionality

## Goal Description
Restore the functionality where the application automatically starts (or enters waiting mode) upon launch if it was previously running (or set to auto-start). This ensures the user doesn't need to manually click "Start" every time the app restarts, especially for off-market hour restarts.

## User Review Required
None. This is a restoration of expected behavior.

## Proposed Changes

### GUI Logic
#### [MODIFY] [Kipo_GUI_main.py](file:///d:/Work/Python/AutoBuy/KipoBuy4.2/Kipo_GUI_main.py)
- Modify `AsyncWorker.load_initial_settings` or [main_loop](file:///d:/Work/Python/AutoBuy/KipoBuy4.2/Kipo_GUI_main.py#82-130) to:
    1. Read `auto_start` boolean from [settings.json](file:///d:/Work/Python/AutoBuy/KipoBuy4.2/settings.json).
    2. If `auto_start` is `True`, automatically trigger `self.schedule_command('start')`.
    - This will leverage existing logic in [schedule_command('start')](file:///d:/Work/Python/AutoBuy/KipoBuy4.2/Kipo_GUI_main.py#182-184) which correctly handles:
        - Market Open -> Starts running.
        - Waiting Period (15:30 - 09:00) -> Enters WAITING mode.
        - Other times (e.g. weekends if not ignored) -> Ready mode (with warning).

